<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1893-11-18T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1893-11-18T00:00:00-05:00" n="661" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d661">
                    <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Gresham</persName> to Mr.
                                <persName type="to">Terrell</persName>.</hi></head>
                    <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                    <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department
                                    of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1893-11-18"><hi rend="italic">November 18,
                            1893</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                    <p>Mr. Gresham acknowledges receipt of Mr. Terrell’s telegram of the 15th,
                        instructs him to protest against punishment of Armenians who have become
                        citizens of the United States as criminals, as well as against their being
                        imprisoned on any ground for too long a time, although admitting that the
                        Porte has the right to expel them and, incidentally, to arrest them for the
                        purpose of expulsion.</p>
                </div>
